and "hired B as a professor."

710
00:45:56,916 --> 00:45:59,586
-My gosh.
-It wasn't in Joon-hwi's petition.

711
00:46:00,253 --> 00:46:03,298
The comma means
that the statements about his donation

712
00:46:03,381 --> 00:46:05,008
and appointment are both true.

713
00:46:06,342 --> 00:46:08,219
-My gosh.
-I didn't even notice it.

714
00:46:08,303 --> 00:46:09,262
Darn it.

715
00:46:11,014 --> 00:46:13,475
You failed to identify it
and correctly apply the law.

716
00:46:13,558 --> 00:46:14,434
Any other comments?

717
00:46:14,517 --> 00:46:15,894
-No, sir.
-Nothing?

718
00:46:15,977 --> 00:46:18,104
Pardon? Oh, I'm sorry.

719
00:46:18,188 --> 00:46:21,733
I assumed it'd be exactly the same
as Joon-hwi's petition,

720
00:46:21,816 --> 00:46:22,775
so I missed it.

721
00:46:22,859 --> 00:46:24,986
Prejudgment can be like a deadly poison.

722
00:46:25,069 --> 00:46:26,821
-Anything else?
-Well…

723
00:46:26,905 --> 00:46:30,950
I should always be alert and focused
as one comma can turn false information

724
00:46:31,034 --> 00:46:32,452
-into facts--
-Then tell me.

725
00:46:32,535 --> 00:46:35,246
If what A wrote is true,
should he be found guilty?

726
00:46:35,330 --> 00:46:39,459
In Korea, it can be considered an offense
even if the statement

727
00:46:39,542 --> 00:46:41,211
-is a fact--
-So is he guilty?

728
00:46:41,878 --> 00:46:44,005
No, I wrote that
he should be found not guilty.

729
00:46:46,549 --> 00:46:47,425
Why?

730
00:46:47,509 --> 00:46:49,177
Article 310 of the Criminal Code.

731
00:46:49,761 --> 00:46:52,514
Even if it's a fact-based
defamatory statement,

732
00:46:52,597 --> 00:46:55,517
the act is not punishable
if the facts are true

733
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:57,268
and solely for the public interest.

734
00:46:57,352 --> 00:46:58,895
It was for the public interest,

735
00:46:58,978 --> 00:47:01,147
-so it is justified.
-Yes.

736
00:47:01,231 --> 00:47:02,273
Joon-hwi, I mean…

737
00:47:02,357 --> 00:47:06,444
A put up the petition demanding the school
clear suspicions surrounding

738
00:47:06,528 --> 00:47:09,948
the donation and the hiring process
and collected signatures

739
00:47:10,031 --> 00:47:12,659
because he was acting
in the public interest as a student--

740
00:47:12,742 --> 00:47:14,410
He could've had a personal agenda.

741
00:47:14,494 --> 00:47:16,454
A and B are related but were on bad terms.

742
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:19,541
Here's the Supreme Court's decision
on Case 98D2188.

743
00:47:19,624 --> 00:47:22,126
"If the primary objective
was for the public interest,

744
00:47:22,210 --> 00:47:25,213
Article 310 of the Criminal Code
cannot be ruled out

745
00:47:25,296 --> 00:47:27,590
even if there was
a personal agenda involved."

746
00:47:28,383 --> 00:47:29,300
So he's not guilty.

747
00:47:31,052 --> 00:47:32,428
-Gosh.
-What the…

748
00:47:33,137 --> 00:47:34,347
She's very smart.

749
00:47:41,312 --> 00:47:44,065
