to write exam questions.

762
00:48:27,859 --> 00:48:29,277
So you can speak with me.

763
00:48:31,821 --> 00:48:35,783
Turns out no one noticed the comma.

764
00:48:35,867 --> 00:48:37,410
Except for me!

765
00:48:37,493 --> 00:48:40,163
Yes. I've become a celebrity
because of that comma.

766
00:48:40,788 --> 00:48:42,790
I got the highest mark in my class.

767
00:48:42,874 --> 00:48:45,460
Kang Byeol! I'm not lying.

768
00:48:47,128 --> 00:48:48,338
I'll call you later.

769
00:48:48,421 --> 00:48:49,547
Excuse me!

770
00:48:51,215 --> 00:48:52,717
NATIONAL FORENSIC SERVICE

771
00:48:54,844 --> 00:48:57,889
Hello, I'm a Hankuk Law student.

772
00:48:57,972 --> 00:48:59,766
Didn't you conduct the second autopsy?

773
00:49:00,391 --> 00:49:02,477
I told the prosecutors everything.
Excuse me.

774
00:49:03,478 --> 00:49:05,063
Any chance that it was manipulated?

775
00:49:05,980 --> 00:49:08,733
I heard no one can reach
the first medical examiner.

776
00:49:09,275 --> 00:49:13,321
And the camera happened to break that day.
Hence, no photos or videos.

777
00:49:14,030 --> 00:49:15,698
I saw this while doing my homework.

778
00:49:15,782 --> 00:49:18,951
He was accused of manipulating one
10 years ago.

779
00:49:21,871 --> 00:49:24,540
There's no way he had missed
what you found.

780
00:49:24,624 --> 00:49:26,376
If he saw it, why did he leave it out?

781
00:49:27,001 --> 00:49:29,087
Unless he was ordered
to frame my professor

782
00:49:29,170 --> 00:49:31,464
for drugging the victim to death.

783
00:49:35,635 --> 00:49:37,345
That's enough. He'd never do that.

784
00:49:49,190 --> 00:49:51,192
CITIZENS' POLICE
FOR OUR RIGHTEOUS NATION

785
00:49:52,235 --> 00:49:53,486
How did the interview go?

786
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:55,697
HAPPY CITIZENS

787
00:49:55,780 --> 00:49:56,948
It wasn't a big deal.

788
00:49:58,574 --> 00:50:00,993
But thanks to you, I'm "the accused" now.

789
00:50:01,077 --> 00:50:03,413
-Did they treat you like a suspect?
-Of course not.

790
00:50:03,496 --> 00:50:05,289
I'm a prosecutor. How dare they--

791
00:50:05,373 --> 00:50:08,126
Drop that attitude and get with the times.

792
00:50:08,209 --> 00:50:11,295
-I'll submit evidence, so you'll--
-What? Be indicted?

793
00:50:12,088 --> 00:50:13,464
You've just been indicted.

794
00:50:15,216 --> 00:50:16,676
I guess you haven't heard.

795
00:50:17,218 --> 00:50:18,511
I've notified the school.

796
00:50:19,262 --> 00:50:21,139
-You're trying too hard.
-Not really.

797
00:50:21,931 --> 00:50:25,601
I bet you thought the two likely causes
of death would be a problem.

798
00:50:25,685 --> 00:50:27,395
But you were wrong.

799
00:50:27,979 --> 00:50:30,231
Both you and Han Joon-hwi
have been indicted.

800
00:50:31,357 --> 00:50:33,151
As joint principal offenders.

801
00:50:33,234 --> 00:50:34,110
JOINT OFFENDERS

802
00:50:34,193 --> 00:50:35,945
That is one groundless conclusion.

803
00:50:36,028 --> 00:50:37,488
It's not groundless.

804
00:50:37,572 --> 00:50:40,867
Han Joon-hwi used such a sneaky trick
to get you out.

805
00:50:40,950 --> 00:50:43,161
If you weren't in on it together,
why would he…

806
00:50:44,370 --> 00:50:45,329
go to such lengths?

807
00:50:45,413 --> 00:50:47,373
Oh, right.

808
00:50:48,708 --> 00:50:50,460
I'm leaking info again, aren't I?

809
00:50:54,797 --> 00:50:57,675
Everyone at the school seems shocked.

810
00:50:59,510 --> 00:51:02,263
Get a lawyer who used to be
a judge or prosecutor this time.

811
00:51:09,812 --> 00:51:12,982
The prosecution delivered
some shocking news earlier today.

812
00:51:14,066 --> 00:51:16,903
Professor Yang and Han Joon-hwi
have been indicted

813
00:51:16,986 --> 00:51:19,363
as joint principal offenders
in the murder.

814
00:51:20,198 --> 00:51:21,115
Pardon me?

815
00:51:21,199 --> 00:51:22,575
"Joint principal offenders"?

816
00:51:23,451 --> 00:51:25,453
I'm sure you're all shocked by the news.

817
00:51:25,536 --> 00:51:26,871
Ms. Oh.

818
00:51:28,790 --> 00:51:30,374
I rushed to call this meeting

819
00:51:31,125 --> 00:51:34,462
to inform you of the school's decision
regarding Professor Yang.

820
00:51:34,545 --> 00:51:36,589
This indictment makes no sense.

821
00:51:36,672 --> 00:51:38,216
They're joint offenders?

822
00:51:39,675 --> 00:51:40,927
Are they writing a novel?

823
00:51:41,010 --> 00:51:44,430
That is for the judge to decide.

824
00:51:45,807 --> 00:51:47,892
Even with the presumption of innocence,

825
00:51:47,975 --> 00:51:50,645
if Professor Yang continues to teach,

826
00:51:50,728 --> 00:51:53,064
it'll lead to more unwanted problems.

827
00:51:54,232 --> 00:51:56,192
So he'll be removed from his position.

828
00:51:56,275 --> 00:51:57,401
-What?
-Gosh.

829
00:51:57,485 --> 00:51:58,778
-Seriously?
-Oh, boy.

830
00:51:58,861 --> 00:51:59,987
Will that be enough?

831
00:52:01,447 --> 00:52:03,115
Shouldn't he be fired?

832
00:52:03,199 --> 00:52:04,992
Isn't it almost the same thing?

833
00:52:06,118 --> 00:52:07,829
Telling him that he can't teach.

834
00:52:07,912 --> 00:52:09,163
No, it's different.

835
00:52:09,664 --> 00:52:11,290
He can keep his professor title.

836
00:52:13,251 --> 00:52:15,628
He can't teach the Criminal Code course
anymore.

837
00:52:15,711 --> 00:52:19,006
Professor Jung,
please continue to fill in.

838
00:52:19,090 --> 00:52:22,593
As for Joon-hwi,
I'll have the vice dean take over.

839
00:52:23,427 --> 00:52:27,265
Joon-hwi submitted his withdrawal letter
this morning.

840
00:52:32,478 --> 00:52:33,813
WITHDRAWAL FORM

841
00:52:41,904 --> 00:52:43,197
CAMPUS DIRECTORY

842
00:52:48,536 --> 00:52:49,912
DISCLAIMER OF INTEREST BY HEIR

843
00:52:54,250 --> 00:52:55,960
-He was cremated?
-Yes.

844
00:53:06,137 --> 00:53:07,847
YANG JONG-HOON

845
00:53:07,930 --> 00:53:10,933
REMOVED FROM CURRENT POSITION
AS OF OCTOBER 26, 2020

846
00:53:11,017 --> 00:53:12,101
"Removed"?

847
00:53:12,184 --> 00:53:14,186
They were both indicted
as joint offenders.

848
00:53:14,270 --> 00:53:17,356
It means they planned the murder together
from the get-go.

849
00:53:18,566 --> 00:53:21,444
We should've seen the whole picture
instead of comparing them.

850
00:53:21,527 --> 00:53:23,321
-This is crazy.
-My gosh!

851
00:53:25,031 --> 00:53:25,865
Hey.

852
00:53:49,347 --> 00:53:50,348
MISCELLANEOUS

853
00:53:52,016 --> 00:53:53,643
HAEWON DAILY_SEO BYUNG-JU

854
00:53:53,726 --> 00:53:55,478
SEO GI-YEOL DIES DURING INVESTIGATION

855
00:53:57,855 --> 00:54:00,274
TOYGOODTOY CEO SEO GI-YEOL DIED BY SUICIDE

856
00:54:03,778 --> 00:54:05,196
SEO BYUNG-JU_LAW_REVIEW

857
00:54:05,279 --> 00:54:07,323
LAW REVIEW_BYUNGJU SEO

858
00:54:19,919 --> 00:54:22,672
They've moved him to a columbarium.

859
00:54:23,631 --> 00:54:25,049
-A columbarium?
-Yes.

860
00:54:31,764 --> 00:54:32,932
MR. SUNG FROM COPY ROOM

861
00:54:34,266 --> 00:54:35,393
Hi, what's up?

862
00:54:36,390 --> 00:54:38,141
SEO BYUNG-JU
REST IN PEACE

863
00:54:41,895 --> 00:54:42,771
I'm sorry.

864
00:54:44,314 --> 00:54:45,607
SEO BYUNG-JU
REST IN PEACE

865
00:54:51,571 --> 00:54:53,198
How dare you set foot in here?

866
00:54:56,201 --> 00:54:58,787
Are you going to flee
now that you've been indicted?

867
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:00,956
You scumbag.

868
00:55:02,124 --> 00:55:04,668
I can't believe you schemed
with Yang Jong-hoon.

869
00:55:05,502 --> 00:55:06,420
"Schemed"?

870
00:55:11,341 --> 00:55:12,509
What's going on?

871
00:55:12,592 --> 00:55:13,969
What are you doing here?

872
00:55:16,096 --> 00:55:17,264
Why did you cremate him?

873
00:55:19,808 --> 00:55:23,812
They dug him up
for the second autopsy,

874
00:55:23,895 --> 00:55:25,230
so burying him again was--

875
00:55:25,313 --> 00:55:26,982
You observed the second autopsy.

876
00:55:28,483 --> 00:55:29,317
Yes, I did.

877
00:55:29,401 --> 00:55:32,320
Were there really signs of bleeding
in his brain?

878
00:55:34,906 --> 00:55:37,617
<i>I couldn't actually observe it</i>
<i>because it was too gruesome.</i>

879
00:55:37,701 --> 00:55:39,286
<i>I fainted, so I saw nothing.</i>

880
00:55:40,954 --> 00:55:42,080
Go help her.

881
00:55:49,087 --> 00:55:50,589
Because it was too gruesome?

882
00:55:50,672 --> 00:55:52,090
Was it not just an act?

883
00:55:52,674 --> 00:55:54,134
What are you talking about?

884
00:55:55,510 --> 00:55:56,803
What are you implying?

885
00:56:03,435 --> 00:56:06,855
<i>Didn't you put on an act to give them time</i>
<i>to manipulate the results?</i>

886
00:56:14,446 --> 00:56:16,573
Come on. Hurry.

887
00:56:16,656 --> 00:56:18,784
What are you suspicious of?

888
00:56:18,867 --> 00:56:21,078
-You said you know the director well.
-I sure do!

889
00:56:21,161 --> 00:56:22,662
-My gosh.
-Long time no see.

890
00:56:22,746 --> 00:56:26,166
The results from the first
and second autopsies don't add up.

891
00:56:26,249 --> 00:56:28,335
I briefly talked to them about the things

892
00:56:28,418 --> 00:56:29,836
that I don't understand.

893
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:32,547
The examiner just said the usual things,
but his assistant…

894
00:56:32,631 --> 00:56:34,841
DIRECTOR'S OFFICE

895
00:56:37,052 --> 00:56:38,220
DIRECTOR'S OFFICE

896
00:56:54,361 --> 00:56:57,781
They were photos of another corpse,
not Professor Seo.

897
00:56:59,199 --> 00:57:00,075
That's not true.

898
00:57:01,660 --> 00:57:03,745
The examiner recorded
this phone conversation.

899
00:57:04,454 --> 00:57:05,956
Shall I play it in front of him?

900
00:57:11,753 --> 00:57:14,881
I said the cause of death has to be
brain hemorrhage from a fall.

901
00:57:14,965 --> 00:57:16,758
I never told you to whip up two causes!

902
00:57:16,842 --> 00:57:18,093
I said it's not true!

903
00:57:22,305 --> 00:57:23,557
What's with that glare?

904
00:57:23,640 --> 00:57:25,392
I didn't do it.

905
00:57:26,643 --> 00:57:27,561
It wasn't me!

906
00:57:33,150 --> 00:57:34,192
Okay, thank you.

907
00:57:35,026 --> 00:57:37,404
The NFS asked them
to launch an investigation,

908
00:57:37,487 --> 00:57:39,573
so the examiner and the wife
have been booked.

909
00:57:40,198 --> 00:57:42,367
Oh, no. Joon-hwi must be shocked.

910
00:57:42,451 --> 00:57:45,328
It proves that he's innocent,
so he should call it even.

911
00:57:45,412 --> 00:57:47,706
I'm impressed that you pulled this off.

912
00:57:48,206 --> 00:57:49,708
All the digging has paid off.

913
00:57:50,208 --> 00:57:52,794
Joon-hwi managed to clear his name,
but Prof. Yang…

914
00:57:53,920 --> 00:57:55,755
Indictment isn't a joke.

915
00:57:55,839 --> 00:57:58,341
Take responsibility for indicting us
as joint offenders.

916
00:58:00,051 --> 00:58:01,803
You practically wrote a novel.

917
00:58:01,887 --> 00:58:04,181
You should attend my lecture
on joint offenders.

918
00:58:10,020 --> 00:58:11,480
Your charges will be dropped.

919
00:58:18,361 --> 00:58:19,529
I've been dismissed.

920
00:58:25,243 --> 00:58:26,786
WITHDRAWAL FORM

921
00:58:46,765 --> 00:58:48,141
You didn't kill him either.

922
00:58:48,725 --> 00:58:50,310
Is there evidence to prove it?

923
00:58:51,269 --> 00:58:52,687
Had you been the killer,

924
00:58:52,771 --> 00:58:55,565
you wouldn't have gotten Sol A
to check Lee Man-ho's alibi.

925
00:58:55,649 --> 00:58:58,652
Maybe I was trying to dump it on him
because I'm the killer.

926
00:58:59,194 --> 00:59:00,570
My alibi hasn't been proven.

927
00:59:01,154 --> 00:59:02,197
Still, I think--

928
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:04,741
If there's no evidence,
it's just an assumption,

929
00:59:04,824 --> 00:59:05,909
which is unlike you.

930
00:59:05,992 --> 00:59:07,410
The sugar packet--

931
00:59:07,494 --> 00:59:09,371
I'm glad they know you didn't take it.

932
00:59:14,459 --> 00:59:15,460
I'm glad…

933
00:59:20,882 --> 00:59:21,758
that you survived.

934
00:59:31,893 --> 00:59:33,395
Wait, just a second.

935
00:59:33,478 --> 00:59:34,354
<i>Too bad.</i>

936
00:59:34,980 --> 00:59:37,107
<i>I'm O Rh negative. But today, I lost</i>

937
00:59:37,190 --> 00:59:38,567
<i>some of my valuable blood.</i>

938
00:59:41,778 --> 00:59:43,071
<i>My blood is valuable.</i>

939
00:59:44,864 --> 00:59:46,616
Can you get his number?

940
00:59:47,284 --> 00:59:48,535
RARE BLOOD COMMUNITY

941
00:59:56,585 --> 00:59:58,044
WE NEED O RH NEGATIVE

942
01:00:01,256 --> 01:00:02,549
Do not give it to him.

943
01:00:04,467 --> 01:00:07,262
Sure, if that's what you want.

944
01:00:08,138 --> 01:00:10,765
Okay, then will you give me
half of your inheritance?

945
01:00:12,183 --> 01:00:13,310
I can't agree to that.

946
01:00:15,478 --> 01:00:17,188
Then I should give him my blood.

947
01:00:18,106 --> 01:00:19,274
I know you won't.

948
01:00:19,899 --> 01:00:21,651
If Prof. Yang dies just like that,

949
01:00:22,652 --> 01:00:24,362
you'd benefit more than I would.

950
01:00:25,322 --> 01:00:26,448
<i>You really think so?</i>

951
01:00:27,824 --> 01:00:29,576
You're in quite a mess yourself.

952
01:00:32,078 --> 01:00:34,623
So I have no reason
not to donate my blood to him.

953
01:01:20,502 --> 01:01:21,961
NEW MAIL

954
01:01:27,425 --> 01:01:28,385
YOU HAVE NEW MAIL

955
01:01:28,468 --> 01:01:30,595
RE: YOUR COPYRIGHT INQUIRY

956
01:01:32,430 --> 01:01:33,640
KOREA COPYRIGHT COMMISSION

957
01:01:33,723 --> 01:01:35,225
READ

958
01:01:37,602 --> 01:01:40,188
HELLO, THIS IS KOREA COPYRIGHT COMMISSION.

959
01:01:40,271 --> 01:01:41,606
INBOX
READ MAIL

960
01:01:43,274 --> 01:01:45,068
YANG JONG-HOON
TRASH

961
01:01:45,151 --> 01:01:46,861
KANG SOL B'S PLAGIARIZED DISSERTATION

962
01:01:47,529 --> 01:01:49,614
<i>MY VIEW ON KANG SOL B'S PLAGIARISM</i>

963
01:01:49,698 --> 01:01:51,491
BY PROFESSOR YANG JONG-HOON

964
01:01:51,574 --> 01:01:52,826
RE: YOUR COPYRIGHT INQUIRY

965
01:01:52,909 --> 01:01:54,119
KOREA COPYRIGHT COMMISSION

966
01:02:01,126 --> 01:02:02,293
<i>Bring me the laptop.</i>

967
01:02:16,808 --> 01:02:18,560
<i>You think I can't find you, right?</i>

968
01:02:22,021 --> 01:02:22,981
PROFESSOR KANG JU-MAN

969
01:02:54,304 --> 01:02:55,972
<i>I bet you saw that too. I'll go see</i>

970
01:02:56,055 --> 01:02:57,515
<i>-the dean tomorrow.</i>
-Prof. Yang!

971
01:02:57,599 --> 01:02:59,517
<i>The one who took the laptop</i>
<i>is the culprit?</i>

972
01:02:59,601 --> 01:03:02,103
<i>You're fired so you can't show up here</i>
<i>ever again.</i>

973
01:03:02,187 --> 01:03:03,438
<i>You look just like her.</i>

974
01:03:03,521 --> 01:03:05,148
<i>Looked like you never come home.</i>

975
01:03:05,231 --> 01:03:06,816
<i>He was watching our house.</i>

976
01:03:06,900 --> 01:03:07,817
Want to talk to you.

977
01:03:07,901 --> 01:03:10,153
<i>I shouldn't ask though I'm curious.</i>
<i>It's insane.</i>

978
01:03:10,737 --> 01:03:11,988
<i>All the suspects are here.</i>

979
01:03:12,071 --> 01:03:14,365
Is this why you didn't let us
read your paper?

980
01:03:14,449 --> 01:03:15,950
<i>I heard you'd met with Prof. Seo.</i>

981
01:03:16,034 --> 01:03:17,410
<i>Why did you search that?</i>

982
01:03:17,494 --> 01:03:19,412
Whoever dies… I'm not scared of that.

983
01:03:19,496 --> 01:03:22,248
<i>If you did something wrong,</i>
<i>you should pay for it.</i>

984
01:03:22,332 --> 01:03:24,375
If Prof. Seo wanted to take issue with it,

985
01:03:24,459 --> 01:03:26,211
<i>would you have wanted to kill him?</i>

986
01:03:26,711 --> 01:03:27,629
<i>Is it me this time?</i>

